    • setHeight

      public void setHeight​(Builder builder, BuildingType height) throws InvalidBuildException, NoMoreMovesException
      This function is responsible for setting a cell's height, which translates to building on a cell.
      Parameters:
      builder - represents the builder which is trying to build on the cell
      height - represents the height at which the builder wants to build
      Throws:
      InvalidBuildException - if the cell is occupied by another builder OR if the cell is not adjacent
      NoMoreMovesException - if the build goes through and the next player has no more moves available

    • getNear

      protected java.util.ArrayList<Cell> getNear()
      Finds cells near the given one.
      Returns:
      list of cells which are near the given cell.

    • isNear

      private boolean isNear​(Cell other)
      This simple function checks whether the " other " Cell is near to this. It is a helper function to getNear().
      Parameters:
      other - Cell to be checked for nearness
      Returns:
      true if near, false otherwise

    • movableCell

      boolean movableCell​(int x, int y) throws InvalidCoordinateException
      Checks whether the given cell is not already occupied
      Parameters:
      x - X coordinate of the cell to be checked
      y - Y coordinate of the cell to be checked
      Returns:
      true if the Cell has no builder nor dome on it, else false
      Throws:
      InvalidCoordinateException - if the given coordinates are invalid
